title: Chicken-apple-beet Salad
summary: You can never have too many side dish recipes, so give Chicken-apple-beet Salad a try. This recipe makes 15 servings with 93 calories, 8g of protein, and 3g of fat each. For 80 cents per serving, this recipe covers 8% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. 44 people were glad they tried this recipe. A mixture of apple juice, oven roasted chicken breast, pecan halves, and a handful of other ingredients are all it takes to make this recipe so yummy. It is a good option if you're following a caveman, gluten free, dairy free, and primal diet. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes roughly 4 minutes. With a spoonacular score of 91%, this dish is super. Similar recipes include Healthy and Delicious: Shredded Beet, Apple, and Currant Salad with Apple Vinaigrette, Beet-and-Apple Salad, and Beet-and-Apple Salad.
